description: Grimsby stretch their unbeaten run to seven games with a draw against managerless Tranmere in League Two.
title: Grimsby Town 1-1 Tranmere Rovers
title_page: League Two: Grimsby Town 1-1 Tranmere Rovers - BBC Sport
maintext:
After winning the reverse fixture in October, Grimsby Town will be looking to complete a first Football League double over Tranmere Rovers since the 1998-99 season.
Tranmere Rovers will be looking to record successive away Football League wins against Grimsby Town for the first time in club history, after beating them 2-1 in this exact fixture last season.
Grimsby have won both of their last two home league games, last winning three in a row within a single season in May 2023.
Tranmere are currently enduring a run of 10 successive away league defeats; since League Two began in 2004, the only club to lose 11 straight away matches within a single campaign in the division were Crewe in April 2011.
